=begin pod
=head2 create-widget-for-value

Creates a widget that can be used as a drag icon for the given C<$value>.

Supported types include strings, B<Gnome::Gdk4::N-RGBA> and L<Gnome::Gtk4::TextBuffer|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/TextBuffer>.
If GTK does not know how to create a widget for a given value,
it will return undefined.

This method is used to set the default drag icon on drag-and-drop
operations started by L<Gnome::Gtk4::DragSource|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/DragSource>, so you don't need to set
a drag icon using this function there.

=begin code
method create-widget-for-value ( N-Object $value --> N-Object )
=end code

=item $value; a B<Gnome::GObject::N-Value>

Return value; A new L<Gnome::Gtk4::Widget|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Widget>
  for displaying C<$value> as a drag icon.. 

